    outlook: "The immediate future will see the Academy closely monitoring the efficacy and member feedback regarding its 'Mandatory Viewing Protocol.' Expect intense internal discussions and potentially further refinements to the rule in upcoming years. Studios and independent producers will be re-evaluating their strategies, possibly prioritizing films with broader international appeal and more diverse genre elements, inspired by 'KPop Demon Hunters.' The success of K-Pop in mainstream awards could also open doors for other non-traditional cultural phenomena to find cinematic expression and recognition. The 2027 Oscars will be a crucial test, revealing whether these changes represent a temporary blip or a permanent paradigm shift in Hollywood.",
    conclusion: "The 2026 Academy Awards will be remembered as a turning point, defined by the groundbreaking victory of 'KPop Demon Hunters' and the Academy's bold, albeit controversial, attempt to redefine its voting integrity. This year's ceremony underscored the unstoppable force of global pop culture and the industry's ongoing struggle to adapt to a rapidly changing world. As the dust settles, one thing is clear: the Oscars, and indeed Hollywood itself, are undergoing a profound transformation, ushering in an era where international appeal and voter accountability are paramount.",
