      bullCase: "The relentless pace of AI innovation and adoption will continue to drive unprecedented corporate earnings growth and capital allocation towards technology. Global economies will show robust resilience, absorbing geopolitical shocks, and central banks will maintain accommodative policies or achieve a \'soft landing,\' fostering a sustained bull market in AI-centric equities.",
      bearCase: "An escalation of the Iran conflict could trigger a severe global energy crisis and supply chain disruptions, leading to a significant economic downturn. Simultaneously, high valuations in the AI sector could correct sharply due to profit-taking, rising interest rates, or regulatory headwinds, leading to a broad market pullback.",
      neutralCase: "Markets will likely remain in a state of dynamic equilibrium, with the powerful tailwinds of AI innovation counterbalanced by persistent geopolitical tensions and cautious monetary policy. Performance will be highly stock-specific, favoring companies with proven AI monetization strategies and strong balance sheets, while broader index gains may moderate.",
      probabilityWeightedOutlook: "A probability-weighted outlook suggests a moderately bullish trajectory (60%) for the remainder of 2026, driven by AI\'s fundamental strength, tempered by a significant probability of market volatility (30%) due to geopolitical risks and potential for sector-specific corrections. A severe bearish outcome (10%) linked to a major global crisis is less likely but remains a tail risk.",
