      neutralCase: "The market is likely to remain highly volatile and sensitive to macroeconomic data in the short term. Bitcoin may consolidate around the $60,000-$65,000 range, with altcoins continuing to show mixed performance. While AI stocks rebound, crypto might not immediately follow, maintaining a period of divergence. Investors will likely adopt a wait-and-see approach until clearer signals emerge from U.S. inflation reports and Federal Reserve policy. Institutional flows via ETFs will remain a key determinant of price action, with neither strong inflows nor outflows dominating.",
      probabilityWeightedOutlook: "A neutral-to-cautiously bullish outlook holds a higher probability in the immediate term. While significant bearish factors persist (ETF outflows, hawkish Fed), Bitcoin\'s ability to rebound from $59,200 demonstrates underlying demand. The market is likely to trade within a range, with a 45% chance of continued consolidation and slight upward pressure if inflation data is benign, a 35% chance of further downside if inflation is hot and ETF outflows accelerate, and a 20% chance of a strong bullish breakout if macro conditions rapidly improve or a major positive catalyst emerges.",
